   "source": [
    "# Exploratory Data Analysis - Predict Customer Churn"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9e368457",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## About this dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "A **telecom customer-churn** dataset: one row per customer, target = **`Churn`** (`Yes` = left, `No` = stayed). Churn = cancelling service; cutting it matters because keeping a customer is far cheaper than acquiring one.\n",
    "\n",
    "**20 features**, in three groups:\n",
    "- **Demographics** - `gender`, `SeniorCitizen`, `Partner`, `Dependents`.\n",
    "- **Account** - `tenure`, `Contract`, `PaperlessBilling`, `PaymentMethod`, `MonthlyCharges`, `TotalCharges`.\n",
    "- **Services** - `PhoneService`, `MultipleLines`, `InternetService` + add-ons (`OnlineSecurity`, `OnlineBackup`, `DeviceProtection`, `TechSupport`, `StreamingTV`, `StreamingMovies`).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key facts:** classes are imbalanced (~**22.5%** churn -> evaluate with ROC-AUC / F1, not accuracy). Train = `train.csv` (~594k rows); `test.csv` is held out for one final check. This notebook does **EDA** to guide feature engineering and modelling."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2f5d4ae3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Setup and data loading"
   ]
  },
